    <div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even" property="schema:articleBody content:encoded"><p>If you have a Drupal 7 site, then you should be using the <a href="https://drupal.org/project/entitycache">Entity cache</a> module, here's why:</p>

<p>Lots and lots of things in Drupal are 'entities', such as the content, the users, the taxonomy terms and if you're using contrib modules like <a href="https://drupal.org/project/field_collection">Field collection</a> or <a href="https://drupal.org/project/eck">ECK</a>, then those are entities too.</p></div></div></div><span rel="schema:url" resource="/drupal-code/you-should-use-entity-cache" class="rdf-meta"></span><span property="schema:name" content="You should use Entity cache" class="rdf-meta"></span>
